.SH NAME
Navigator.geolocation \- Navigator: geolocation property
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Secure context:\f[R] This feature is available only in secure
contexts (HTTPS).
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]Navigator.geolocation\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property
returns a \f[CR]Geolocation\f[R] object that gives Web content access to
the location of the device.
This allows a website or app to offer customized results based on the
user\[cq]s location.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] For security reasons, when a web page tries to access
location information, the user is notified and asked to grant
permission.
Be aware that each browser has its own policies and methods for
requesting this permission.
.RE
.SH VALUE
A \f[CR]Geolocation\f[R] object.
